The Quaeriſt ſaith, That the Votes of the Independents in the Houſes were arbitrarie, exorbitant, and irregular, and that they diſpoſed and fingred more of the common Treaſure then others: That whole Quaere, I believe, is falſe and

ſlanderous;
57 E. 3. c. 17. and the Author ought to make it good, or elſe to undergoe the Law of Talion; which is, to ſuffer ſuch puniſhment, failing of his proofe, as the accuſed ſhould, in caſe of proofe made.
